The 21-year-old netted in the 9th and 39th minutes with the former assisted by South Africa’s Percy Tau for Club Brugge, who looked on course for a stunning win over Real Madrid in the Spanish capital until second-half replies from Sergio Ramos and Casemiro ensured the game ended 2-2. Elsewhere, Algerian Yassine Benzia was sent off for two bookable offences in Olympiakos’ 3-1 loss away to Red Star Belgrade, while Younes Belhanda, Christian Luyindama, Jean-Michael Seri and Sofiane Feghouli couldn’t prevent a home defeat for Galatasaray at the hands of Paris Saint-Germain. Ghanaian star Thomas Partey scored a 58th minute goal to help Atletico Madrid claim a 2-0 win over Lokomotiv Moscow in Russia, Riyad Mahrez assisted Raheem Sterling’s goal in Manchester City’s 2-0 triumph over Dinamo Zagreb, while Serge Aurier and Tottenham Hotspur had a nightmare game at home as they suffered a 7-2 thrashing at the hands of German heavyweights Bayern Munich. --AfricaSports--